body: Gobstopper, 5.11-. On the same wall as a prior post. Hard to figure out the beginning… and the temperature/shade was not on my side. The cold rock made the moves feel insecure. Fell off the beginning sequence probably four times. Two clean laps after. This is a video from part of the first clean go. It shows a left heel hook that was way too hard and totally unnecessary. The second go felt much easier without. Coming back in the spring and leading the few 5.11s on this wall (when Tobi’s bigger!) will be a blast.
